=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Line_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright clean sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 1695 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1695.1410
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.0059
  harmonic_regularity: 0.4450
  pitch_clarity: 10.3032
  inharmonicity: 0.1907
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.5471
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Line Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Line.html
// Tags: Line, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// XLine is usually better than Line for frequency
play({ SinOsc.ar(Line.kr(200, 17000, 10), 0, 0.1) });
